race.comment: Tough. GUIDO (2) peaks and made further improvement stepping up to this trip at Moonee Valley third-up. He commenced this preparation off a 487-day break and is still well shy of his metro best. On song, this is winnable. THURMOND (11) comes out of the same race where he was wide early and was just fair through the line. He's better than that and rates to make the finish in this lineup. MR LINCOLN (1) won a Maiden hurdle at Ballarat and then delivered again this grade/trip at trip at Mt Gambier on the flat. We know he'll run it right out and maps to get every chance. DON STEFANO (4) peaks on a 6-day return. Longer trips are likely to be his go.
